        "impact": "MEDIUM",
        "sector": "BROAD_MARKET",
        "reason": "The postponement of U.S. military strikes on Iran has improved global risk sentiment, reflected in the significant rally of U.S. stocks. This positive global development will likely have a cascaded bullish effect on Indian indices like Nifty and BankNifty, primarily through improved foreign sentiment and potential increased FII inflows into emerging markets like India. However, geopolitical tensions inherently increase market volatility.",
