      "id": "8a25f76a-dbe6-45ca-97cd-6e9e338a784b",
      "title": "Oil, weak flows weigh on rupee outlook, says UBS strategist Bhanu Baweja",
      "description": "Bhanu Baweja, Chief Strategist at UBS Investment Bank, said foreign inflows into India are unlikely to recover meaningfully as high crude prices weigh on earnings and valuations. With added pressure from the trade balance and remittances, he expects the rupee to remain under stress despite RBI efforts to curb volatility. He noted that the rise in bond yields— with India’s 10-year at 6.78%, the highest since January 2025—reflects a sharp repricing of rate expectations, not fiscal concerns. As the shock is supply-driven, he expects limited scope for aggressive rate hikes, with yields likely to stabilise or ease.",
      "content": "Bhanu Baweja, Chief Strategist at UBS Investment Bank, said foreign inflows into India are unlikely to recover meaningfully as high crude prices weigh on earnings and valuations. With added pressure from the trade balance and remittances, he expects the rupee to remain under stress despite RBI efforts to curb volatility. He noted that the rise in bond yields— with India’s 10-year at 6.78%, the highest since January 2025—reflects a sharp repricing of rate expectations, not fiscal concerns. As the shock is supply-driven, he expects limited scope for aggressive rate hikes, with yields likely to stabilise or ease.",
      "source": "CNBC TV18",
      "url": "https://www.cnbctv18.com/videos/economy/india-rupee-pressure-crude-fpi-flows-bond-yields-bhanu-baweja-ubs-19873375.htm",
