      "title": "Oil supply crunch to keep global markets under pressure: Arvind Sanger",
      "description": "Geopolitical tensions and surging energy prices are forcing investors to prioritize liquidity and cash over traditional safe havens like gold. Oil prices are now the central market driver, with a structural supply imbalance and potential Strait of Hormuz disruptions posing significant macroeconomic risks. Emerging markets face varied impacts, with energy exporters better positioned than importers.",
